about.summary: nexusformat: Python API to access NeXus data

name: nexusformat
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "nexusformat" %}
{% set version = "0.4.20" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: "58023fe0913a6d8273afc971cdc64ec0fc909f5d7d39a7819df0674ca2108ec2"

build:
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - nxstack=nexusformat.scripts.nxstack:main
  noarch: "python"
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv "

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools
    - numpy
  run:
    - h5py
    - numpy
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - nexusformat
    - nexusformat.nexus
    - nexusformat.scripts
  commands:
    - nxstack --help

about:
  home: "https://nexpy.github.io/nexpy/"
  license: "BSD-3-Clause"
  license_family: "BSD"
  license_file: "COPYING"
  summary: "nexusformat: Python API to access NeXus data"
  doc_url: "https://nexpy.github.io/nexpy/"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/nexpy/nexusformat"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - tschoonj
    - rayosborn
